<h1 align="center">**Developer Portfolio Template**</h1>

<div align="center">
This Developer Portfolio Template is a responsive website for showcasing developer skills and projects, deployed automatically using a Jenkins CI/CD pipeline with GitHub webhooks. As a DevOps engineer, I built this to demonstrate automated deployment workflows, ensuring instant updates to GitHub Pages on every code push.
</div>

<br>

<h2 align="center">**Features**</h2>

<h2 align="center">**Features**</h2>

<div align="center">
- **Automated deployment** to GitHub Pages via Jenkins CI/CD pipeline with GitHub webhook triggers.<br>
- **Responsive portfolio template** for showcasing developer skills and projects.<br>
- **Fixed header** with hamburger menu for mobile-friendly navigation.<br>
- **Project case studies** for e-commerce, task management, and portfolio sites.<br>
- **Contact form** for inquiries (requires backend integration).<br>
- **Social media integration** with links to LinkedIn, GitHub, Twitter, YouTube, and Instagram.
</div>

<br>

<h2 align="center">**Technologies Used**</h2>

<div align="center">
- **Jenkins**: Automates CI/CD pipeline for seamless deployment.<br>
- **GitHub Webhooks**: Triggers pipeline on code pushes to the main branch.<br>
- **GitHub Pages**: Hosts the static portfolio site.<br>
- **Git**: Manages version control for the repository.<br>
- **HTML5, CSS3 (SASS), JavaScript, React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS**: Core technologies for the portfolio template.<br>
- **Google Fonts (Source Sans Pro)**: Provides clean typography.<br>
- **Shopify, WordPress, Google Ads, Facebook Ads**: Leveraged in past projects.
</div>

<br>

